Create Mutations for UI to pass through uploaded spreadsheet data to back end and to consume summary/validations from mongo. Upload Schema: {
  submissionId: <string> //UI generated
  listType: <string> "Global ASAP", //Hardcoded for now, will need to come from a system property for default. Will support bin later
  listItems: <array<item>> [
    {
        Identifier <string> (ISIN/CUSIP number)
        Side <string>
        Quantity <number>
        LimitLevel <number>
        TargetLevel <number>
        Settlement Date <date>
        internalNotes <string>
    }
] Once payload received from UI, append fields not sent from UI (or this can be done by validation service) then simple pass through to KStream Validation Service Summary Schema: UI will subscribe to this data from rfq-validations collection. {SubmissionId: <string>, UserId:<string>, Acknowledged:<bool>, Passed: <number>, Failed: <number>, FailedDetails<[FailedDetail]>: [
    {
      Identifier <string> (ISIN/CUSIP number)
      Side <string>
      Quantity <number>
      LimitLevel <number>
      TargetLevel <number>
      Settlement Date <date>
      internalNotes <string>
      rejectionReason <string>
    }
  ]
} There are no dependencies on creating these schema’s - unlocks UI workflow.

We want to be able to reset dealer selections both Open Trading and Disclosed Counterparties with one api call. Currently in the dealer api we can only do one at a time, which means we have to make 2 calls to reset selections. Want to be able to do: dealerSelectionMutation({
      payload: {
        userId: Number(userId),
        id: Number(rowId),
        disclosedCounterParties: [],
        selectedGroupDistributionList: [],
        dealerGroup: '',
        selectionId: lastSelectionId+1,
        disclosedOtDealers: []
      },
}); At the moment we are making 2 separate calls when targeted RFQ is toggled to reset both selections.

This epic is to house the work required to build out process trades in XPro 2.0 A  process trade  is: A trade whose price and size are negotiated and agreed bilaterally (usually over voice) and then entered into a trading platform purely for execution processing, confirmation, and reporting. The platform is used to  process the trade , not to price discover or negotiate. When entering a process trade via the UI, client:- Selects the Process Trade flag Enters the Pre-Agreed economic information Enters a list of competing quotes Note; Dealer that is available for process trade should not incorporate filter on inventory Figma Links Manual:  Prototype  ,  Screens Auto-Accept:  Prototype ,  Screens Tech Work Required (notes to be moved to Jiras) Add 2 new field to xpro-activity-console processRFQEligibility<bool> isProcessRFQChecked<bool> Create mutation for isProcessRFQChecked user action Mutation stored in memory for submission processTradeInquiryMutation({
      payload: {
        versionId: 1
        processTrade: isChecked,
        inquiryId: rowId,
        competingQuotes: []
      },
    }); UI trigger mutation with optimistic update when toggling Process trade can be initiated via Changing the Trade Type in the details panels right-click → Process Trade from AC (this will effectively pre-select the process panel) Note can only be for singles - UI needs to check the BE flag before displaying this option on context menu (disable or hide the option) What happens if line item already selected and details panel visible then client right click → process (same action as changing trade type)? Disclosed Ctpty Section changes to “Executing Cpty” (when isProcessRFQChecked) Only allow single selection Single selection must be made to enable “Submit” Update Submit button text (updated enabled logic) (when isProcessRFQChecked) Enabled logic = TBC Create UI screen for adding competing quotes (when isProcessRFQChecked) BE function to populate collection with competing quotes? Re…

Validation service should be a reusable service that can be used for validations of both solicited (editing existing fields) or unsolicited (creating new RTS). Validation steps should be identical for either flow however some differences occur for when editing existing inquiries due to refreshing both AutoX eligibility as well as refreshing latest errors and warnings. See architecture diagram    for full flow. Schema’s Required: Incoming (From UI): Unsolicited RFQ: {
  submissionId: <string> //UI generated
  listType: <string> "Global ASAP", //Hardcoded for now, will need to come from a system property for default. Will support bin later
  listName: <string> //Create based on user name + current time??
  maAccountId: <string> //current user id
  listCount: <number> //maybe not needed, should be a count of listItems
  listItems: <array<item>> [
    {
        id: <string> {UI Generated}
        Identifier <string> (ISIN/CUSIP number)
        Side <string>
        Quantity <number>
        LimitLevel <number>
        TargetLevel <number>
        Settlement Date <date>
        internalNotes <string>
    }
] Solicited RFQ (Edits): Atomic update, UI will pass the full list of fields on every update. {
        version: {UI Increment}
        id: <string> {UI Generated}
        Side <string>
        Quantity <number>
        LimitLevel <number>
        TargetLevel <number>
        Settlement Date <date>
        internalNotes <string>
    } Outgoing (XPro Internal) Summary: UI requires acknowledgment of number of inquiries passed/failed. Failed inquiries require additional detail. Summary should be a streaming output of how many have passed validation (sent to Carnonical) and how many failed Publish summary (schema below) to rfq-validations (can be renamed if needed). {SubmissionId: <string>, Passed: <number>, Failed: <number>, FailedIds: [<items>]} 
