Any change made in the UI needs to be sent down to canonical Create new Schema for GFQ mutation when editing any field. This mutation will be an atomic update so UI will send all fields that are available to UI. Fields can be nullable (either field not populated on UI or user has cleared the field purposefully). Note the inclusion of the version. UI will increment the version to ensure latest update from DB matches UI optimistic state. This version must be passed on to persistence {
  version: {UI Increment}
  id: <string> {UI Generated}
  Side <string>
  Quantity <number>
  LimitLevel <number>
  TargetLevel <number>
  Settlement Date <date>
  InternalNotes <string>
}

